  "instructions": [
    "Heat the avocado oil in a deep frying pan to 375°F.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix together the Agemono batter mix, lime juice, orange juice, cayenne pepper, paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the Monterey jack cheese to the bowl and toss to coat.",
    "Dip the cheese into the hot oil and fry for 2-3 minutes, or until golden brown.",
    "Using a slotted spoon, remove the cheese from the oil and place it on a paper towel-lined plate to drain excess oil.",
    "Repeat the frying process with the remaining cheese.",
    "Meanwhile, chop the fresh cilantro and slice the jalape\u00125.",
    "Once the cheese is done, place it on the slate tile vessel and top with chopped cilantro and sliced jalape\u00125.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
